meta:
  origin:
    producer: FAO, OECD, and Millennium Ecosystem Assessment
    title: Projections of peak agricultural land
    description: |-
      This dataset combines actual reported trends in global agricultural land area from the UN Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) from 1961–2014, with future projections from various sources.

      Data for the period 1961–2014 is based on the metric "Agricultural land" from the FAO database. Agricultural land includes arable land, permanent crops, and meadows and pasture land.

      Projections to 2050 are based on those reported in the OECD Environmental Outlook to 2050 (2012). The original projection sources include FAO (2006) World Agriculture Towards 2030/2050, the International Assessment of Agricultural Knowledge, Science and Technology for Development (IAASTD, 2009), and the Millennium Ecosystem Assessment (MEA, 2005).
    citation_full: 'FAO (UN Food and Agriculture Organisation) (2006). World Agriculture Towards 2030/2050. FAO, Rome. OECD (2012). OECD Environmental Outlook to 2050: The Consequences of Inaction. Available at: http://www.oecd.org/environment/indicators-modelling-outlooks/oecdenvironmentaloutlookto2050theconsequencesofinaction.htm. Millennium Ecosystem Assessment (2005). Synthesis Report. Island Press, Washington, DC.'
    url_main: http://www.fao.org/faostat/en/#data/RL
    date_accessed: '2026-03-05'
    date_published: '2012'
